The article discusses the response to the Deepwater Horizon explosion and BP oil spill. President Obama held a meeting with Cabinet members and senior staff to review BP's efforts to stop the oil leak and decide on next steps. The President emphasized the importance of engaging independent experts and bringing different perspectives to find solutions. Energy Secretary Chu will lead a team to have a dialogue with BP officials to pursue potential solutions. The President also stated that BP will be responsible for all costs and compensation for damages. Additionally, the President requested legislation to Congress to update the law surrounding caps on damages caused by oil spills. Various government officials and agencies participated in the meeting.